Honestly one of my favorite professors at UTSC. She very passionate about what she teaches and is very approachable and kind. She gives very detailed instructions for assignments and her marking is fair. She is very accommodating and continues to use student feedback to help restructure her classes. I would 100% recommend taking D levels with her

Gives way too many large assignments within a short time span. Within about a month and a half, we were given: less than 1 week to write a 12+ page paper, a project with a group poster presentation and a report, an in class data analysis lab which we need for our final paper which is due less than a week after the project is due.
Passionate professor who did an excellent job explaining fairly complicated ideas. The homework kept you from procrastinating and if you did it you got a boost in your overall grade.
